sub_title: Customer Service Coordinator for Luxury Retail and E-commerce
summary:
Thanks to my interest for different languages and cultures I studied for years French, English and Chinese. In particular, my studies in Chinese Culture at Venice Ca'Foscari University made me fall in love with this language. Experiences abroad (one year in France, one year and a half in China) helped me to became a "citizen of the world" and improve my Chinese, French and English.
Two years as a Sales Assistant for luxury and fashion brands helped me to discover Retail and different approaches to shopping and customer experience. Completing a Master in Luxury and Fashion Management gave me the opportunity to enter the in this world with new skills.
